defs.docs:
Pull parser for [CommonMark](https://commonmark.org). This crate provides a [Parser](struct.Parser.html) struct
 which is an iterator over [Event](enum.Event.html)s. This iterator can be used
 directly, or to output HTML using the [HTML module](html/index.html).

defs.name: html
defs.docs: HTML renderer that takes an iterator of events as input.

defs.name: push_html
defs.docs:
Iterate over an `Iterator` of `Event`s, generate HTML for each `Event`, and
 push it to a `String`.

defs.name: write_html
defs.value: fn <'a, I, W> (writer: W, iter: I) -> io::Result<()>
defs.docs:
Iterate over an `Iterator` of `Event`s, generate HTML for each `Event`, and
 write it out to a writable stream.

defs.name: Fenced
defs.docs: The value contained in the tag describes the language of the code, which may be empty.

defs.name: CodeBlockKind
defs.docs: Codeblock kind.

defs.name: Paragraph
defs.docs: A paragraph of text and other inline elements.

defs.name: Heading
defs.docs: A heading. The field indicates the level of the heading.

defs.name: CodeBlock
defs.docs: A code block.

defs.name: List
defs.docs:
A list. If the list is ordered the field indicates the number of the first item.
 Contains only list items.

defs.name: Item
defs.docs: A list item.

defs.name: FootnoteDefinition
defs.docs:
A footnote definition. The value contained is the footnote's label by which it can
 be referred to.

defs.name: Table
defs.docs: A table. Contains a vector describing the text-alignment for each of its columns.

defs.name: TableHead
defs.docs:
A table header. Contains only `TableRow`s. Note that the table body starts immediately
 after the closure of the `TableHead` tag. There is no `TableBody` tag.

defs.name: TableRow
defs.docs: A table row. Is used both for header rows as body rows. Contains only `TableCell`s.

defs.name: Link
defs.docs: A link. The first field is the link type, the second the destination URL and the third is a title.

defs.name: Image
defs.docs: An image. The first field is the link type, the second the destination URL and the third is a title.

defs.name: Tag
defs.value: Tag::{Paragraph, Heading, BlockQuote, CodeBlock, List, Item, FootnoteDefinition, Table, TableHead, TableRow, TableCell, Emphasis, Strong, Strikethrough, Link, Image}
defs.docs: Tags for elements that can contain other elements.

defs.name: Inline
defs.docs: Inline link like `[foo](bar)`

defs.name: Reference
defs.docs: Reference link like `[foo][bar]`

defs.name: ReferenceUnknown
defs.docs: Reference without destination in the document, but resolved by the broken_link_callback

defs.name: Collapsed
defs.docs: Collapsed link like `[foo][]`

defs.name: CollapsedUnknown
defs.docs: Collapsed link without destination in the document, but resolved by the broken_link_callback

defs.name: Shortcut
defs.docs: Shortcut link like `[foo]`

defs.name: ShortcutUnknown
defs.docs: Shortcut without destination in the document, but resolved by the broken_link_callback

defs.name: Autolink
defs.docs: Autolink like `<http://foo.bar/baz>`

defs.name: Email
defs.docs: Email address in autolink like `<john@example.org>`

defs.name: LinkType
defs.value: LinkType::{Inline, Reference, ReferenceUnknown, Collapsed, CollapsedUnknown, Shortcut, ShortcutUnknown, Autolink, Email}
defs.docs: Type specifier for inline links. See [the Tag::Link](enum.Tag.html#variant.Link) for more information.

defs.name: Start
defs.docs:
Start of a tagged element. Events that are yielded after this event
 and before its corresponding `End` event are inside this element.
 Start and end events are guaranteed to be balanced.

defs.name: End
defs.docs: End of a tagged element.

defs.name: Text
defs.docs: A text node.

defs.name: Code
defs.docs: An inline code node.

defs.name: Html
defs.docs: An HTML node.

defs.name: FootnoteReference
defs.docs:
A reference to a footnote with given label, which may or may not be defined
 by an event with a `Tag::FootnoteDefinition` tag. Definitions and references to them may
 occur in any order.

defs.name: SoftBreak
defs.docs: A soft line break.

defs.name: HardBreak
defs.docs: A hard line break.

defs.name: Rule
defs.docs: A horizontal ruler.

defs.name: TaskListMarker
defs.docs: A task list marker, rendered as a checkbox in HTML. Contains a true when it is checked.

defs.name: Event
defs.value: Event::{Start, End, Text, Code, Html, FootnoteReference, SoftBreak, HardBreak, Rule, TaskListMarker}
defs.docs:
Markdown events that are generated in a preorder traversal of the document
 tree, with additional `End` events whenever all of an inner node's children
 have been visited.

defs.name: None
defs.docs: Default text alignment.

defs.name: Alignment
defs.docs: Table column text alignment.

defs.name: Options
defs.docs:
Option struct containing flags for enabling extra features
 that are not part of the CommonMark spec.

defs.name: Parser
defs.docs: Markdown event iterator.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new event iterator for a markdown string without any options enabled.

defs.name: new_ext
defs.docs: Creates a new event iterator for a markdown string with given options.

defs.name: new_with_broken_link_callback
defs.value:
fn (text: &'a str, options: Options, broken_link_callback:
    Option<&'a dyn Fn(&str, &str) -> Option<(String, String)>>) -> Parser<'a>
defs.docs:
In case the parser encounters any potential links that have a broken
 reference (e.g `[foo]` when there is no `[foo]: ` entry at the bottom)
 the provided callback will be called with the reference name,
 and the returned pair will be used as the link name and title if it is not
 `None`.

defs.name: into_offset_iter
defs.docs:
Consumes the event iterator and produces an iterator that produces
 `(Event, Range)` pairs, where the `Range` value maps to the corresponding
 range in the markdown source.

defs.name: OffsetIter
defs.docs: Markdown event and source range iterator.

defs.name: StringTooLongError
defs.docs:
Returned when trying to convert a `&str` into a `InlineStr`
 but it fails because it doesn't fit.

defs.name: InlineStr
defs.docs:
An inline string that can contain almost three words
 of utf-8 text.

defs.name: Boxed
defs.docs: An owned, immutable string.

defs.name: Borrowed
defs.docs: A borrowed string.

defs.name: Inlined
defs.docs: A short inline string.

defs.name: CowStr
defs.docs:
A copy-on-write string that can be owned, borrowed
 or inlined.
